  "text": "This gradient is the difference of two conditional expectations over the feature vector f: a \"clamped\" expectation that is conditioned on the observed words and tags (w, t) and a \"free\" expectation that is only conditioned on the words in the text, w, and ignores the sentence-level labels. To make the inference tractable, we use a Viterbi approximation that replaces the expectations with maximization. Because each sentence corresponds to more than one temporal tag, the maximization of the \"clamped\" maximization is somewhat challenging to compute. We use the approximate inference algorithm of [CITATION_1] , that views inference as a weighted set cover problem, with worst case running time (|T | · |W |), where |T | is the number of all possible temporal tag values and |W | is the number of words in a sentence.",
